	Youth for peace  
	Twenty-three youths from Bangladesh, India, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka attended a five-day workshop, titled South Asian Youth for Peace in Nepal in June. Of these, four were from India.         
	The workshop was organised by NGO Asian Resource Foundation, Nepal. It addressed the challenges faced by the youth in south Asia.         
	The students, aged between 18 and 25 years, participated in various interactive tasks, including drawing their own model of a peaceful world. The workshop saw religious leaders from various faiths  including Hinduism, Buddhism, Christianity, Islam and the Bahai  speak on peace. The participants also presented a peace declaration, formulated by themselves, to the Prime Minister of Nepal.         
